PART 1: Basic paste-in (read system clipboard, send text to PTY as keyboard input)
PART 2: Bracketed paste (wrap pasted text in ESC[200~ / ESC[201~ markers when the terminal app has enabled mode 2004)

Key design constraints:
- Must branch from upstream master (magiblot/tvterm), NOT from feature/text-selection. The paste feature is completely independent.
- Follow the same architectural patterns as the text-selection implementation.
- tvterm-core changes should be in termview.cc/termctrl.cc/vtermemu.cc. App-level command wiring in source/tvterm/.
- Clipboard reading: platform-native tools (pbpaste on macOS, xclip/xsel on Linux). Mirror the write path from text-selection but in reverse.
- Bracketed paste mode 2004: libvterm tracks terminal modes. Find how to query whether the child app has enabled bracketed paste mode, and wrap accordingly.
- Threading: paste is initiated from the main thread (UI event). Text must be sent to the PTY via the existing event/write path (TerminalController::sendEvent or similar). Do NOT write directly to PTY from main thread.
- Add cmPaste command constant to TVTermConstants following existing pattern (cmCopySelection etc).
- Menu item "Paste" alongside existing "Copy Selection".
- Key binding: Shift+Insert (standard terminal paste).

Research and document:
1. Exact code paths for sending text to PTY (how does keyboard input flow today?)
2. How libvterm exposes mode 2004 (bracketed paste mode) state
3. Whether TerminalEvent needs a new event type for paste, or if we can reuse KeyDown
4. Platform clipboard read implementation (reverse of the write in termview.cc copySelection)
5. Wide character / UTF-8 handling considerations
6. Security considerations (paste bombing, control characters)

Output a single markdown file PLAN-paste.md with the same structure and quality as PLAN-text-selection.md. Include design decisions, implementation steps, file-by-file changes, and test scenarios.
